Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Development Engineer* position with *Amazon Connect*. I bring over three years of professional experience in building scalable, distributed systems and AI-powered solutions, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the technical depth and operational rigor this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected an AI-powered customer experience layer that translates natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1,000+ distributed endpoints — requiring rigorous design of fault-tolerant, low-latency systems with end-to-end automated customer actions. To ensure operational excellence, I implemented a full observability infrastructure using Langfuse and LangSmith, covering tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks, reducing latency by 60% and costs by 50%. I also built scalable, multi-threaded orchestration using LangChain and LangGraph with Object Oriented Design patterns, enabling concurrent tool execution across microservices in complex distributed systems. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Java, Spring Boot, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handles file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO via expiring signed URLs — demonstrating multi-tiered, distributed architecture design with SOA principles. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with high availability, and developed fault-tolerant workflows using AWS Step Functions and Lambda for long-running data imports, ensuring operational excellence in distributed systems. Together, these roles have prepared me to own code end-to-end from design to development and deliver secure, scalable, resilient systems while maintaining constant customer focus.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in AI/ML, full software development life cycle management, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture Amazon values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on an HPC cluster, managing the full software development life cycle from data preparation to model deployment. I was responsible for implementing scalable model inference using vLLM with Hugging Face deployment, ensuring secure, fault-tolerant model serving for production workloads. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor, thinks long-term about system design, and communicates clearly — all of which I would bring to the Amazon Connect team. Beyond my technical work, I have mentored junior engineers on AI/ML integration, code reviews, and design patterns for building resilient, highly available systems, directly mirroring the mentorship and knowledge-sharing responsibilities central to this role.

I have always been passionate about customer obsession, passion for invention, commitment to operational excellence, and long-term thinking, and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of Amazon's mission to be Earth's most customer-centric company, Earth's best employer, and Earth's safest place to work. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

